   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-a" mid="40" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Read the poem April gave you.)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="8"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>I recently came across this poem about <FONT color=#a82424>thirteen alpacas running in the plains</FONT>, but I find it hard to understand the poem.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-b" mid="41" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>What the heck is this?!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="9"><![CDATA[<html>$Thirteen Alpacas$<BR><FONT color=#086171>Thirteen alpacas running in the plains.
(Better take different route not to cause any pain.)
<BR>Alpaca One says I'm scared, Alpaca Two repeats I'm scared, Alpaca Three...</FONT><FONT color=#7e12d2>(</FONT><FONT color=#7e12d2>It goes on and on)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-c" mid="42" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(My mind is blank.)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>Precisely! I don't understand what it's about but I somehow feel the terrible anxiety and fear in the alpacas. The root of that fear is substituted as a derivation from the alpaca's own self and amplified the catharsis of anti-realistic and modernist poetry, don't you think so?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-d" mid="43" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Beats me...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>Simply speaking, I can sense a form of <FONT color=#2b2723>grievance</FONT> in this poem.<BR>What made the alpacas run with such sorrow?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-d" image="QW_108.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-e" mid="44" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Really?!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-e" mid="45" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Come to think of it, I think I've seen it too!</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-e" mid="46" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Mistland sure is a mystical land.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>What's even more amazing is that alpacas that run without any reason really exist in the <FONT color=#a82424>Blue Wind Plains</FONT>!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-1-f" mid="47" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>I want to delve deeper into this poem. That means I need to find out the poet's intentions and background.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-2" mid="48" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Sure.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>So if it's all right with you, can you meet Mr. Bard who wrote this poem and ask him why and how he came to write such a masterpiece?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="59"><![CDATA[<html>$Crazy Mad Bard$<BR>Poetry… It's all about interacting with the universe…….</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-2" image="QW_107.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$Merchant April$<BR>From what I know, Bard is at <FONT color=#a82424>Broken Goldstone Canyon</FONT> right now. You can meet him there.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-2-a" mid="51" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Ask him about his intentions on writing the poem.)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="16"><![CDATA[<html>$Crazy Mad Bard$<BR>Who art thou...? What brings thou hither...?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-2-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-2-b" mid="52" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Well, I guess so…?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$Crazy Mad Bard$<BR>So you're curious about the story of the scared alpaca and the scary alpaca.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-2-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-2-c" mid="53" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>I think so.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>$Crazy Mad Bard$<BR>Fine. But Miss April has not seen the running alpacas for herself, I believe?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-2-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-3" mid="54" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(My mind is blank.)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$Crazy Mad Bard$<BR>If she wants to know the true meaning of the poem, she should go and take a look at the alpacas herself.<BR>Though the poem is expressed in words, it gains life and soul from the real phenomena in this world.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1877_gold_mad_bard-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="20"><![CDATA[<html>$Crazy Mad Bard$<BR>Tell the lady to see the worldly phenomenon clasp with the soul of the poem with her own eyes. That's how she can fully appreciate my poem.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1871_trader_april-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1871_trader_april-3-a" mid="55" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Tell her what Bard said.)</html>]]></talk_answer>
